documentation.text:
@dev
 | The Trust Anchor Storage is the contract responsible for maintaining the chain-of-custody for all of the attestations on the Shyft Core architecture.
 | The primary design goals are to concentrate attestations into individual accounts, with the responsibility of maintenance of those attestations belonging to the Trust Anchors that has initially posted those attestations.
 | To prevent attestation "spam" (invalid attestations that end-users don't agree with), there is a signature provided by both the Trust Anchor and the end-user.
 | After attestation (prior to signatures), the connected Cache Graph contract can be used to map users to Trust Channels (which are the higher level connectivity to the Trust Anchor network) in an "un-consented" manner, after signatures, the Cache Graph can be used to map users to "consented" Trust Channels.
 |
 | There are two ways of managing who provides the permissions for the act of data retrieval.
 | One mechanism is a Managed context, where the end-user is giving permission to the Trust Anchor to fully manage the act of data transmission and retrieval on the user's behalf.
 | The other mechanism is an Un-managed context, where the end-user is the only entity that has permission to allow data transmission from the source Trust Anchor (that has provided the initial attestation) to another Trust Anchor.
 |
 | The contents of the attestation consist of:
 | 1. The end user's smart contract address that is being attested to.
 | 2. The jurisdiction of the attestation (may be different than the Trust Anchor's jurisdiction).
 | 3. The effective (start) time of the attestation (in Seconds from Unix Epoch Time).
 | 4. The expiry time of the attestation (in Seconds from Unix Epoch Time).
 | 5. Any non-PII public metadata (hash codes from the Trust Anchor, etc.)
 | 6. The document matrix, a series of 0's and 1's corresponding to the availability of specific pieces of "hard" documentation that the Trust Anchor holds. Generally encrypted via symmetric AES to prevent abstracted PII from being leaked on the blockchain directly.
 | 7. The availability address, an ethereum-type address corresponding to the smart contract that manages the various economic & regulatory conditions of data transfer from a Trust Anchor to a data retriever. Generally encrypted via symmetric AES to prevent abstracted PII from being leaked on the blockchain directly.
 | 8. Whether this attestation is managed by the Trust Anchor. This indicates that consent conditions are applied from the Trust Anchor instead of the end user.
 |
 | Administrators of this contract are able to be set in order to allow for better management practices, with multi-signature support from the Administrable contract.
@dev Event for the setting of an attestation.
@dev Event for an attestation already existing when attempting setAttestation.
@dev Event for an attestation not being valid when attempting setAttestation.
@dev Event for the revoking of an attestation.
@dev Event for the re-enabling of an attestation.
@dev Event for the main phase of the revocation process
@dev Event for the recompilation phase of the revocation process
@dev Event for enabling the data retrieval in a Managed context.
@dev Event for enabling the data retrieval in a Un-managed context.
@dev Event for revoking the data retrieval in a Managed context.
@dev Event for revoking the data retrieval in an Un-managed context.
@dev Event for a User setting their data retrieval revenue share in respect to a Trust Anchor.

@dev Event for a data retrieval entity (receiving a user's pii data) to confirm that they have validated that the pieces of data sent from the source Trust Anchor are consistent with the data retrieval parameters.
@dev Mapping of the attestation keccak hash to the data model of the attestation, which would contain all pertinent properties of an attestation.
@dev Mapping of the Trust Anchor address to the attestation keccak array that they have set.
@dev Mapping of the attestation keccak hash to the identified address (end user)'s address that is associated with this attestation originally.
@dev Mapping of the identified address (end user)'s address to the associated attestation array.
@dev Mapping of the attestation keccak hash to the Index in the identified address (end user)'s attestation array.
@dev Mapping of the mapping of the end-users relation between themselves, their pii-maintaining trust anchor, and their current data revenue share.
@dev Address for the Trust Anchor Manager that is linked to this contract.
@dev Address for the Shyft Cache Graph that is linked to this contract.
@dev Initializes Trust Anchor Storage with the owner set to the calling public address.

addDataRetrievalTargetFromIdentifiedAddr.details: | Enables and provides parameters to the data that is consented to be retrieved by the target Trust Anchor.      | This function is called by the end user as it is in the Un-managed context.

params._dataRetrievalTarget: The public address of the Trust Anchor that is doing the data retrieval.
params._documentsRetrievalConsentedEncrypted: The document matrix of the data that is consented to be able to be retrieved by the Trust Anchor that is performing the data retrieval. This is a series of 0's and 1's corresponding to the availability of specific pieces of "hard" documentation that the Trust Anchor holds. Generally encrypted via symmetric AES to prevent abstracted PII from being leaked on the blockchain directly.

returns.result: | 0 = data retrieval target trust anchor is not verified    | 1 = attestation is not managed by the end user    | 2 = not the identified address that this attestation targets    | 3 = attestation already has this data retrieval target    | 4 = data retrieval target set

addDataRetrievalTargetManaged(bytes32,ad.details: | Enables and provides parameters to the data that is consented to be retrieved by the target Trust Anchor.      | This function is called by the Trust Anchor as it is in the Managed context.

params._dataRetrievalTarget: The public address of the Trust Anchor that is doing the data retrieval.
params._documentsRetrievalConsentedEncrypted: The document matrix of the data that is consented to be able to be retrieved by the Trust Anchor that is performing the data retrieval. This is a series of 0's and 1's corresponding to the availability of specific pieces of "hard" documentation that the Trust Anchor holds. Generally encrypted via symmetric AES to prevent abstracted PII from being leaked on the blockchain directly.

returns.result: | 0 = trust anchor is not verified    | 1 = data retrieval target trust anchor is not verified    | 2 = attestation is not managed by trust anchor    | 3 = not the trust anchor address that created this attestation    | 4 = attestation already has this data retrieval target    | 5 = data retrieval target set

changeCurrentAdminConfirmationThreshold(.details: | This function takes in an index for a proposal ot change the current administrator confirmation threshold.      | Uses Multi-signature permissions.

params._proposalIndex: The index for a specific proposal to change the current administrator confirmation threshold.

returns.result: | 0 = not an administrator    | 1 = invalid proposal index    | 2 = not enough administrators to achieve confirmation threshold    | 3 = proposal has expired    | 4 = not enough administrators have permissioned change    | 5 = admin confirmation threshold set

constructor.details: Initializes Trust Anchor Storage with the owner set to the calling public address.

dataRetrievalEntityValidateAttestation(b.details: Validates that the data retrieval was performed in a consented manner by the Trust Anchor performing the data retrieval.

returns.result: | 0 = attestation does not exist    | 1 = attestation cannot be signed by the trust anchor that set the attestation    | 2 = attestation data source(s) have not been sent to this entity    | 3 = attestation already validated by this entity    | 4 = attestation validated

getAdminAccess(address).details: Gets the level of access for a specific administrator.

returns.result: the level of access for this administrator

getAdminConfirmationProposal(uint32).details: Gets the components of a specific NofM change proposal.

returns.adminThreshold: the threshold of the NofM voting within this proposal
returns.endTime: the end time of this proposal, after which it cannot be voted on
returns.isCompleted: whether this proposal has been completed by multisig parties

getAdminConfirmationThreshold().details: Gets the NofM threshold currently required for passing multisig votes.

getAttestationAllValidations(bytes32).details: Gets all of the Validated (data retrieval confirmed) status(es) of an attestations from all data retrievers for this attestation, then returns all of the addresses for all of the data retrievers.

returns.validationEntities: an array of all addresses that have had validations for this attestation

getAttestationComponents(bytes32).details: Gets all of the data from the initial attestation, plus the trust anchor address (the "identified address" must be known already to call this function)

returns.effectiveTime: the effective (start) time of the attestation (in seconds from unix epoch time).
returns.expiryTime: the expiry time of the attestation (in seconds from unix epoch time).
returns.isManaged: whether the address is managed or un-managed
returns.jurisdiction: the Jurisdiction of the attestation (may be different than the trust anchor's jurisdiction)
returns.publicData: any non-pii public metadata (hash codes from the trust anchor, etc.)
returns.trustAnchorAddress: the address of the trust anchor that set this attestation

getAttestationComponentsInKeccakArray(ad.details: Gets all of the data from the initial attestation, plus the trust anchor address (the "identified address" must be known already to call this function)

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.effectiveTime: the effective (start) time of the attestation (in seconds from unix epoch time).
returns.expiryTime: the expiry time of the attestation (in seconds from unix epoch time).
returns.identifiedAddressToTrustAnchorDataRetrie: the revenue share between the end-user and the trust anchor for this attestation
returns.isManaged: whether the address is managed or un-managed
returns.jurisdiction: the Jurisdiction of the attestation (may be different than the trust anchor's jurisdiction)
returns.publicData: any non-pii public metadata (hash codes from the trust anchor, etc.)
returns.trustAnchorAddress: the address of the trust anchor that set this attestation

getAttestationCurrentIdentifiedAddress(b.details: | Gets the (current) address of the end user that is associated to this attestation.      | Note: There is no mechanism within this Trust Anchor Storage architecture to change the attestation, but it may need to be supported in the future.

returns.identifiedAddress: the current address of the end user that is associated to this attestation

getAttestationDataRetrievalsArrayLengthI.details: | Gets the number of data retrievers that have been able to retrieve the source data associated to this attestation.      | Note 1: These data retrievers may or may not have had the ability to retrieve data disabled.      | Note 2: These data retrievers may or may not have already confirmed the results of retrieving the data.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.arrayLength: the length of the array of number of data retrievers that have been able receive this attestation.

getAttestationDataWasSentToRetrievalEnti.details: Gets whether the attestation's source data was sent to the Data Retrieval Entity by the Trust Anchor source.

params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.attestationWasSentToDataRetrievalEntity: a boolean yes/no which corresponds to the data having been marked "sent" by the data sender.

getAttestationDataWasSentToRetrievalEnti.details: Gets the time (in UTC seconds) at which the attestation's source data was sent to the Data Retrieval Entity by the Trust Anchor source.

params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.attestationWasSentToDataRetrievalEntityT: the time (in utc seconds) which corresponds to the data having been marked "sent" by the data sender.

getAttestationIdentifiedAddressToTrustAn.details: Gets the end user's revenue share percentage (as a [64 bits].[64 bits] 128bit base-2 number) to their pii-maintaining Trust Anchor for this attestation.

returns.identifiedAddressToTrustAnchorDataRetrie: the end user's revenue share percentage (as a [64 bits].[64 bits] 128bit base-2 number) to their pii-maintaining trust anchor for this attestation.

getAttestationIsRetrievableFromRetriever.details: Gets the Retrievable (data retrieval able to be done) status of an attestations, for a specific data retriever, for this attestation.

params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.isRetrievable: the retrievable status of the attestation for this specific data retriever

getAttestationIsRetrievableFromRetriever.details: Gets the Retrievable (data retrieval able to be done) status of an attestations, for a specific data retriever, for this attestation.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.
params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.isRetrievable: the retrievable status of the attestation for this specific data retriever

getAttestationIsSentToRetrieverInKeccakA.details: Gets whether the attestation's source data was sent to the Data Retrieval Entity by the Trust Anchor source.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.
params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.attestationWasSentToDataRetrievalEntity: a boolean yes/no which corresponds to the data having been marked "sent" by the data sender.

getAttestationIsValidFromRetriever(bytes.details: Gets the Validated (data retrieval confirmed) status of an attestations, for a specific data retriever, for this attestation.

params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.isValid: a boolean yes/no of whether the attestation is set to 'valid' by a specific data retriever

getAttestationIsValidFromRetrieverInKecc.details: Gets the Validated (data retrieval confirmed) status of an attestations, for a specific data retriever, for this attestation.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.
params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.isValid: a boolean yes/no of whether the attestation is set to 'valid' by a specific data retriever

getAttestationKeccakArrayForIdentifiedAd.details: Gets the entire array of attestations for a specific end user.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.

returns.keccakArray: the entire array of attestations for a specific end user

getAttestationKeccakArrayForTrustAnchor(.details: Gets the entire array of attestations for a specific Trust Anchor.

params._trustAnchorAddress: The Trust Anchor's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.

returns.keccakArray: the entire array of attestations for a specific trust anchor

getAttestationKeccakArrayLengthForIdenti.details: Gets the number of attestations for a particular end user.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.

returns.keccakArrayLength: the length of the user's attestation array

getAttestationKeccakArrayLengthForTrustA.details: Gets the number of attestations for a particular Trust Anchor.

params._trustAnchorAddress: The Trust Anchor's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.

returns.keccakArrayLength: the length of the trust anchor's attestation array

getAttestationKeccakToIdentifiedAddressA.details: Gets the mapping of a hash for an attestation to the index in the array for the end user that this attestation is associated with.

returns.keccakArrayIndex: the index in the end users array of attestation that this hash corresponds to.

getAttestationOriginalIdentifiedAddress(.details: Gets the (original) address of the end user that is associated to this attestation.

returns.identifiedAddress: the original address of the end user that is associated to this attestation

getAttestationRetrievableDocumentsEncryp.details: Gets the Retrievable (data retrieval able to be done) data (generally encrypted) that represent the documents able to be retrieved from an attestations, for a specific data retriever, for this attestation.

params._retrieverAddress: The address of the data retriever that has been able to retrieve the source data from this attestation.

returns.consentedDocumentsEncrypted: the encrypted retrievable data of the attestation for this specific data retriever

getAttestationStatusApprovedInKeccakArra.details: Gets the attestation approved status for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.attestationStatusApproved: the approval status of this attestation (which corresponds to effective time / expiry time, etc)

getAttestationTrustAnchorAddress(bytes32.details: Gets the address of the Trust Anchor that performed the attestation.

returns.trustAnchorAddress: the address of the Trust Anchor for this attestation

getAttestationTrustAnchorIndex(bytes32).details: Gets the Index of the Trust Anchor that performed the attestation.

returns.trustAnchorIndex: the Index of the Trust Anchor for this attestation

getAttestationValidationsArrayLengthInKe.details: Gets the length of the Validated (data retrieval confirmed) results for this attestation.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.arrayLength: the length of the array of data retriever validated results for this attestation

getAttestationValiditySignaturesInKeccak.details: Gets the actual signatures (currently user and trust anchor) for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.validityTrustAnchorSignatureV: #1/3 parts of the signature for the trust anchor that is associated with this attestation
returns.validityTrustSignatureRS: #2/3 and #3/3 parts of the signature for the trust anchor that is associated with this attestation
returns.validityUserSignatureRS: #2/3 and #3/3 parts of the signature for the end user that is associated with this attestation
returns.validityUserSignatureV: #1/3 parts of the signature for the end user that is associated with this attestation

getConsentAvailableInKeccakArray(address.details: Gets the consent available status (number of signatures for this attestation, currently user and trust anchor) for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.consentAvailable: the consent available status (number of signatures for this attestation, currently user and trust anchor) for this attestation

getDataRetrievalRevenueShare(address,add.details: Gets the current data retrieval revenue share relationship between the end user (in this case, msg.sender) and their pii-maintaining TA.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._trustAnchorAddress: The trust anchor that will be trusted to transmit data on the users behalf (covers manage and un-managed contexts).

returns.dataSharePercentage: the data share percentage as a fixed point decimal representation (6 decimals for the input precision (0.000001% minimum sharing = "1", "1000000" = 1.0%, "100000000" = 100.0%))

getGraphConstructableAttestationInKeccak.details: Gets what is considered "graph constructible" outputs for a specific attestation. it contains all of the cross-mapping required to retrieve further data.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.attestationStatusApproved: the approval status of this attestation (which corresponds to effective time / expiry time, etc)
returns.trustAnchorIndex: the Index of the Trust Anchor that set this attestation

getIndexedAttestationAvailabilityAddress.details: Gets the attestation availability for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.availabilityAddressEncrypted: the attestation availability for the specific index of attestations associated with the end user

getIndexedAttestationEffectiveTimeForIde.details: Gets the effective time for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.effectiveTime: the effective time for the specific index of attestations associated with the end user

getIndexedAttestationExpiryTimeForIdenti.details: Gets the expiry time for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.expiryTime: the expiry time for the specific index of attestations associated with the end user

getIndexedAttestationJurisdictionForIden.details: Gets the jurisdiction for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.jurisdiction: the jurisdiction for the specific index of attestations associated with the end user

getIndexedAttestationKeccakHashForIdenti.details: Gets the keccak hash for a specific attestation within the end user's attestation array.

params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.
params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular end user.

returns.keccakHash: the keccak hash for the specific index of attestations associated with the end user

getIndexedAttestationKeccakHashForTrustA.details: Gets the keccak hash for a specific attestation within the Trust Anchor's attestation array.

params._index: The index of the attestation within the array of attestations associated with a particular Trust Anchor.
params._trustAnchorAddress: The Trust Anchor's smart contract address that this attestation is associated to.

returns.keccakHash: the keccak hash for the specific index of attestations associated with the trust anchor

getNumAdminConfirmationProposals().details: Gets the number of a specific NofM change proposal.

returns.result: the number of a specific NofM proposals

getPermissionsForMultisignKey(bytes32).details: Gets whether there have been a specific number of multisignature confirmations for a specific vote.

params._keyKeccak: A hash to reference as the key/value vote subject.

setAttestation(address,uint16,uint64,uin.details: | Sets an attestation for a specific Shyft end-user, sent by a (Verified) Trust Anchor.      | Contains all the information required to perform a lookup for the "hard" or "light" identity, via the "document matrix", as defined in the Shyft Bluepaper [ insert website link here ].      | The "availability address" is a public address that contains the smart contract code for dealing with escrows for identity payment, restrictions, regulatory rules etc.      | Symmetric AES encryption is a preferable way of encoding the "document matrix" and the "availability address", as these could contain (maximally) abstracted PII in the form of bit fields containing the documents that can be retrieved.      | Given the nature of smart contract operation, any subsequent updates that rely on "effectiveTime" and "expiryTime" will need further calls to update the Shyft Cache Graph for full status updates within the Shyft Core architecture flow regarding the current validity of attestations to end-user's accounts.

params._availabilityAddressEncrypted: The availability address, an ethereum-type address corresponding to the smart contract that manages the various economic & regulatory conditions of data transfer from a Trust Anchor to a data retriever. Generally encrypted via symmetric AES to prevent abstracted PII from being leaked on the blockchain directly.
params._documentsMatrixEncrypted: The document matrix, a series of 0's and 1's corresponding to the availability of specific pieces of "hard" documentation that the Trust Anchor holds. Generally encrypted via symmetric AES to prevent abstracted PII from being leaked on the blockchain directly.
params._effectiveTime: The effective (start) time of the attestation (in Seconds from Unix Epoch Time).
params._expiryTime: The expiry time of the attestation (in Seconds from Unix Epoch Time).
params._identifiedAddress: The end user's smart contract address that is being attested to.
params._isManaged: Whether this attestation is managed by the Trust Anchor. This indicates that consent conditions are applied from the Trust Anchor instead of the end user.
params._jurisdiction: The jurisdiction of the attestation (may be different than the Trust Anchor's jurisdiction).
params._publicData: Any non-PII public metadata (hash codes from the Trust Anchor, etc.)

returns.result: | 0 =  trust anchor is not verified               | 1 =  attestation not valid               | 2 =  attestation already exists               | 3 =  attestation set (returns resultAttestationKeccak != 0)
returns.resultAttestationKeccak: resultant keccak hash of the attestation. used for further referencing within the shyft core architecture.

setDataRetrievalRevenueShare(address,uin.details: Sets the data retrieval revenue share relationship between the end user (in this case, msg.sender) and their pii-maintaining TA. This is encoded in each attestation by that TA for this particular user. The user may, at any time, change this relationship, but only for future attestations. Given that while consent is directed by the user (or managed on their behalf by their TA), the TA actually performs the data transmission actions off-chain, and so there is no situation where the TA could unwillingly be front-ran by the user.

params._dataSharePercentage: The percentage, as a fixed point decimal representation (6 decimals for the input precision (0.000001% minimum sharing = "1", "1000000" = 1.0%, "100000000" = 100.0%))
params._trustAnchorAddress: The trust anchor that will be trusted to transmit data on the users behalf (covers manage and un-managed contexts).

returns.result: | 0 = revenue share >100%     | 1 = set revenue share

setDataSenderDidSendDocuments(bytes32,ad.details: | Indicates that the source trust anchor has sent the data/documents (example usage: for the contestation phase in an escrow "availability" contract) to the data retrieval entity.      | This function is called by the source trust anchor that has the user's PII data, on an attestation that has already been permissioned to a data retrieval entity.

params._dataRetrievalTarget: The public address of the Trust Anchor that is doing the data retrieval.

returns.result: | 0 = message sender is not the trust anchor that originally set this attestation    | 1 = data is not set to retrievable with that data retrieval target    | 2 = data was already marked as sent    | 3 = data is now marked as sent
